de.joshuagleitze.trees.towns

Class Main

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.joshuagleitze.trees.towns.Main

  • public class Main
extends java.lang.Object
    Contains the main-method for this program. Starts an interactive console where you can input towns and their number of inhabitants with insert town:number. Single towns can be searched with search town. All inserted values can be printed with info. The order of the output is specified by the traverse type command line parameter.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Joshua Gleitze

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        The main method initialises the program and contains the main while loop for command execution.
        Parameters:
        args - This program expect either one or none command line parameter that specifies the traverse type for the info command. Specify it in the form of tarverse=type where type is one of pre-order, level-order or in-order. If you don't specify a command line parameter, the in-order traverse type will be selected.
